{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011dh3UDSfdr7ujQueNbXnk2","type":"tool_result","content":"   690→are replayed through the wiring so downstream steps receive the same inputs.\n   691→\n   692→### `cloche status`\n   693→\n   694→```\n   695→cloche status [<run-id>] [--all]\n   696→```\n   697→\n   698→With a run ID, shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and\n   699→per-step results.\n   700→\n   701→Without a run ID, shows a daemon status overview: version, run statistics (past hour),\n   702→and active runs. In a project directory, also shows project name, concurrency, and\n   703→orchestration loop state. Use `--all` to show global stats instead of project-specific\n   704→stats.\n   705→\n   706→| Flag | Description |\n   707→|------|-------------|\n   708→| `--all` | Show global stats instead of project-specific stats. |\n   709→\n   710→### `cloche list`\n   711→\n   712→```\n   713→cloche list [flags]\n   714→```\n   715→\n   716→Lists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n   717→Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited to a fixed number.\n   718→\n   719→| Flag | Description |\n   720→|------|-------------|\n   721→| `--all` | Show runs from all projects (default: current project only). |\n   722→| `--project, -p DIR` | Filter by project directory. |\n   723→| `--state, -s STATE` | Filter by run state (`pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`). |\n   724→| `--limit, -n NUM` | Limit the number of results returned. |\n   725→| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n   726→\n   727→### `cloche logs`\n   728→\n   729→```\n   730→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n   731→```\n   732→\n   733→| Flag | Description |\n   734→|------|-------------|\n   735→| `--step, -s <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   736→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   737→| `--follow, -f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   738→| `--limit, -l <n>` | Display only the last n lines of output. |\n   739→\n   740→Flags are combinable: `cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f`\n   741→\n   742→Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   743→\n   744→### `cloche poll`\n   745→\n   746→```\n   747→cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n   748→```\n   749→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0eab4ce-8004-4e9c-9ad4-4515133169d1","uuid":"e01a161e-d707-4e9a-82fa-e5a6d4f2e939","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:23:36.534Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"are replayed through the wiring so downstream steps receive the same inputs.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status [<run-id>] [--all]\n```\n\nWith a run ID, shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and\nper-step results.\n\nWithout a run ID, shows a daemon status overview: version, run statistics (past hour),\nand active runs. In a project directory, also shows project name, concurrency, and\norchestration loop state. Use `--all` to show global stats instead of project-specific\nstats.\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--all` | Show global stats instead of project-specific stats. |\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [flags]\n```\n\nLists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\nResults can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited to a fixed number.\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--all` | Show runs from all projects (default: current project only). |\n| `--project, -p DIR` | Filter by project directory. |\n| `--state, -s STATE` | Filter by run state (`pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`). |\n| `--limit, -n NUM` | Limit the number of results returned. |\n| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step, -s <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow, -f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n| `--limit, -l <n>` | Display only the last n lines of output. |\n\nFlags are combinable: `cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f`\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n```\n","numLines":60,"startLine":690,"totalLines":994}}}
